history.content:
<md>Interested in learning how to write code for quantum computers? Quantum Computing at Berkeley will be holding two workshops on creating and simulating circuits in the Cirq Python library this Wednesday, November 4th, 6-7:30pm. 

**EDIT**: This event has passed, but we've included the materials in the links below, for your perusal. The second slide in each link should contain the relevant materials. Please let us know if you see any issues or have any questions.

For beginners that have no experience with quantum computing, but have taken an introductory linear algebra class and know how to code in Python, we’ll be implementing an algorithm known as Bernstein-Vazirani in our [Beginner Workshop](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1WRphtMsB0MTVEPRJzFzHWLgb7K_2CX7C-05zDHxNsW4/edit?usp=sharing).

For intermediate learners, who have taken or are taking a course on quantum computing, such as CS191, we’ll be implementing Grover’s Search algorithm in our  [Intermediate Workshop](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/19TmkI58UtY5BmQwu38iEnT6sXVDw3i8jykOaJtzTs3c/edit?usp=sharing).
</md>
